<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870116-0099 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Fay's Drug Co.'s RhodesAnd Herrmann Quit Posts</HL><DD> 01/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS FAY </IN><DATELINE> LIVERPOOL, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Fay's Drug Co. said Daniel A. Herrmann resigned as president, and Peter E. Rhodes as executive vice president, to pursue their respective &quot;business and personal interests.&quot;    The discount drugstore chain said Henry A. Panasci, chairman and chief executive officer, also would serve as president until a successor to Mr. Herrmann is named.    Messrs. Herrmann and Rhodes also resigned as directors. </TEXT></DOC>